{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775850424195,"sessionID":"ses_287142419ffeQOq2kV3FLICynY","part":{"id":"prt_d78ebe7ea001AqobfmFwChkJCc","messageID":"msg_d78ebdcbc001RRfILDBSF9yMtG","sessionID":"ses_287142419ffeQOq2kV3FLICynY","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_f482c38a5662452f8a52e928","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube project structure","prompt":"Thoroughly explore the agentcube project structure. I need to understand:\n\n1. The overall project layout - what directories exist at the root and key subdirectories\n2. The cmd/cli module specifically - what files exist there, what commands are already implemented\n3. How existing CLI commands are structured (look at any existing command implementations)\n4. Any existing task.md or similar planning files to understand the format used\n5. Any design documents related to ST-3 or pack command\n6. The project's testing patterns and frameworks used\n7. Any configuration files (pyproject.toml, setup.py, etc.) that define how the CLI is packaged\n\nSearch broadly: look for patterns like \"pack\", \"bundle\", \"archive\", \"export\" in the codebase.\nAlso look for any spec documents, ADRs, or design docs.\n\nReturn a comprehensive summary of:\n- Project structure overview\n- cmd/cli module contents and patterns\n- Existing command implementation examples (show file paths and key code snippets)\n- Testing patterns\n- Any relevant design/spec documents\n- Package configuration details","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_2871404faffeY7CDAMEBOr2j0m (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nI now have a comprehensive understanding of the project. Here is the complete summary:\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Project Analysis: AgentCube\n\n### 1. Project Structure Overview\n\n```\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/\n```\n\nThis is a **Go-based Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform** for AI agents, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`. The project also has a **planned but not-yet-implemented Python CLI** component.\n\n**Root-level directories:**\n\n| Directory | Purpose |\n|-----------|---------|\n| `cmd/` | Go binary entry points (4 binaries) |\n| `pkg/` | Go library packages (shared logic) |\n| `client-go/` | Generated Kubernetes typed client, informers, listers |\n| `changes/` | Change request folders (AR-001 through AR-020) |\n| `cli-toolkit/` | Design/spec docs for the Python CLI |\n| `python-sdk/` | Design/spec docs for the Python SDK |\n| `testing/` | TDD manifest document |\n| `ci-cd/` | CI/CD design/spec |\n| `deployment/` | Deployment design, client-go docs |\n| `sandbox-orchestration/` | Sandbox orchestration design/spec |\n| `session-routing/` | Session routing design/spec |\n| `session-store/` | Session store design/spec |\n| `code-execution/` | Code execution design/spec |\n| `idle-cleanup/` | Idle cleanup design/spec |\n| `integrations/` | Integration design/spec |\n\n**Root-level files:**\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `go.mod` / `go.sum` | Go module definition (Go 1.25.0) |\n| `project.md` | Project context overview |\n| `design.md` | **AR-020: CLI pack command -- Full Design** (798 lines, fully populated) |\n| `proposal.md` | AR-019: CLI Binary Entry (4 binaries) proposal |\n| `delta-spec.md` | AR-016: PicoD File Management API delta spec (870 lines) |\n| `test_spec.md` | TDD specification with test case requirements |\n| `.sdd_prompt.md` | SDD (Software Design Document) prompt used to generate design.md |\n| `coverage.out` | Go test coverage output |\n\n---\n\n### 2. The `cmd/` Module -- Go Binary Entry Points\n\nThe `cmd/` directory contains **4 Go binaries**, following the standard Go project layout:\n\n```\ncmd/\n├── agentd/          # K8s Controller -- sandbox idle cleanup (EXISTING)\n│   └── main.go      # 59 lines, uses controller-runtime\n├── picod/           # Sandbox Daemon -- code execution inside pods (EXISTING)\n│   └── main.go      # 15 lines, delegates to picod.ParseFlags()\n├── router/          # HTTP Router -- session-aware proxy (NEW in AR-019)\n│   ├── config.go    # Flag parsing (18 flags, env var fallback)\n│   └── main.go      # 74 lines, Gin-based HTTP server\n└── workloadmanager/ # Workload Manager -- sandbox lifecycle API (NEW in AR-019)\n    ├── config.go    # Flag parsing (14 flags, env var fallback)\n    └── main.go      # 164 lines, Gin-based HTTP server with CRUD endpoints\n```\n\n**Key pattern for Go binaries:**\n- Each binary has its own `main.go` (and optionally `config.go`)\n- Config parsing uses `flag.NewFlagSet` (not global flags) for testability\n- Environment variable fallback via `envOr(key, defaultVal)` helper\n- Kubeconfig resolution: explicit flag -> in-cluster config -> `~/.kube/config`\n- Graceful shutdown via signal handling (SIGINT/SIGTERM)\n- Uses `klog` for logging (not `log.Printf`)\n\n**There is NO `cmd/cli/` directory yet.** The Python CLI is described in docs but has zero actual Python files in the repository.\n\n---\n\n### 3. cmd/cli Module -- Current State\n\n**CRITICAL FINDING: The `cmd/cli/` directory does NOT exist.** There are **zero Python files** (`.py`) anywhere in the project. The Python CLI is entirely a design/spec artifact that has been documented in exhaustive detail but not yet implemented.\n\nThe planned structure (from `design.md` and `cli-toolkit/design.md`) is:\n\n```\ncmd/cli/\n├── pyproject.toml                     # Python package config\n├── agentcube/\n│   ├── __init__.py                    # __version__ = \"0.1.0\", exports\n│   ├── cli/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py\n│   │   └── main.py                    # Typer app, all commands\n│   ├── models/\n│   │   └── pack_models.py             # MetadataOptions dataclass\n│   ├── runtime/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py                # Re-exports runtimes\n│   │   ├── pack_runtime.py            # PackRuntime\n│   │   ├── build_runtime.py           # BuildRuntime\n│   │   ├── publish_runtime.py         # PublishRuntime\n│   │   ├── invoke_runtime.py          # InvokeRuntime\n│   │   └── status_runtime.py          # StatusRuntime\n│   ├── services/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py\n│   │   ├── metadata_service.py        # AgentMetadata, MetadataService\n│   │   ├── docker_service.py          # DockerService\n│   │   ├── k8s_provider.py            # KubernetesProvider\n│   │   └── agentcube_provider.py      # AgentCubeProvider\n│   └── operations/\n│       └── __init__.py                # Placeholder\n└── examples/\n    ├── hello-agent/main.py\n    └── math-agent/main.py\n\n```\n\n**Planned CLI commands (5 total):**\n\n| Command | Runtime Class | Purpose |\n|---------|--------------|---------|\n| `pack` | `PackRuntime` | Validate workspace, generate Dockerfile, merge metadata |\n| `build` | `BuildRuntime` | Build container image (local Docker or cloud) |\n| `publish` | `PublishRuntime` | Deploy to K8s (AgentRuntime CR or standard Deployment) |\n| `invoke` | `InvokeRuntime` | POST JSON to published agent endpoint |\n| `status` | `StatusRuntime` | Display agent status in Rich Table |\n\n**Console script entry point:** `kubectl-agentcube = \"agentcube.cli.main:app\"`\n\n---\n\n### 4. Existing CLI Command Implementation Patterns\n\nSince no Python code exists yet, the \"implementation patterns\" come entirely from the design documents. Here is how commands are structured:\n\n**Typer app setup** (from `cli-toolkit/design.md`):\n```python\napp = typer.Typer(\n    name=\"agentcube\",\n    help=\"AgentCube CLI - A developer tool for AI agent lifecycle management.\",\n    no_args_is_help=True,\n    rich_markup_mode=\"rich\",\n    add_completion=False\n)\n```\n\n**Root callback** (global options):\n```python\n@app.callback()\ndef main(\n    version: Optional[bool] = typer.Option(None, \"--version\", callback=version_callback, is_eager=True),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\", \"-v\"),\n) -> None:\n    if verbose:\n        logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n```\n\n**Command pattern** (example: `pack`):\n```python\n@app.command()\ndef pack(\n    workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\", show_default=True),\n    agent_name: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--agent-name\"),\n    language: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--language\"),\n    entrypoint: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--entrypoint\"),\n    port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--port\"),\n    build_mode: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--build-mode\"),\n    description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\"),\n    output: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--output\"),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\"),\n) -> None:\n    with Progress(SpinnerColumn(), TextColumn(\"[progress.description]{task.description}\"), transient=True) as progress:\n        task = progress.add_task(\"Packaging agent...\", total=None)\n        try:\n            runtime = PackRuntime(verbose=verbose)\n            workspace_path = Path(workspace).resolve()\n            result = runtime.pack(workspace_path, agent_name=agent_name, ...)\n            progress.update(task, description=\"Done\")\n            console.print(f\"[green]✓[/green] Agent '{result['agent_name']}' packaged successfully!\")\n        except Exception as e:\n            _handle_error(e, \"packaging agent\", verbose)\n```\n\n**Error handling pattern:**\n```python\ndef _handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool) -> None:\n    console.print(f\"[red]Error {command_name}: {e}[/red]\")\n    if verbose:\n        console.print_exception()\n    raise typer.Exit(1)\n```\n\n**Runtime class pattern** (example: `PackRuntime`):\n- Constructor takes `verbose: bool = False`\n- Public method: `pack(workspace_path: Path, **options: Any) -> Dict[str, Any]`\n- Private methods prefixed with `_` for each step of the pipeline\n- Depends on `MetadataService` for YAML load/save operations\n- Returns a dict with result keys (`agent_name`, `workspace_path`, `metadata_path`)\n\n---\n\n### 5. Change Request (AR) Document Format\n\nEach change request in `changes/AR-XXX/` follows a consistent 4-file structure:\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `proposal.md` | Purpose, scope, impact analysis, alternatives, acceptance criteria |\n| `design.md` | Technical implementation details (architecture, data structures, API contracts, code samples) |\n| `delta-spec.md` | Gherkin-style scenarios extending the base spec |\n| `tasks.md` | Task breakdown with checkboxes, dependency graph, acceptance criteria table |\n\n**ST-3 reference:** \"Stage ST-3 (Design)\" is the design completion stage. All tasks.md files have a precondition: `Stage ST-3 (Design) completed`.\n\n**AR-020 (CLI pack command)** is the most recent and most fully documented change:\n- `design.md`: Fully populated (798 lines) with complete implementation code\n- `delta-spec.md`: Fully populated (313 lines) with 30+ Gherkin scenarios\n- `proposal.md`: Fully populated (272 lines)\n- `tasks.md`: **Skeleton only** -- contains TODO placeholders, not yet filled in\n\n---\n\n### 6. Testing Patterns\n\n**Go testing** (what exists):\n- Framework: Standard `testing` package + `github.com/stretchr/testify/assert`\n- File naming: `*_test.go` alongside source files\n- 28 test files found across the project\n- Pattern: Table-driven tests, `assert.Equal()` for assertions\n- Run with: `go test ./... -v -count=1`\n- Race detection: `go test -race ./...`\n- Code quality: `go vet ./...`, `go mod tidy`\n\n**Example Go test** (`pkg/router/config_test.go`):\n```go\nfunc TestNewDefaultConfig(t *testing.T) {\n    cfg := NewDefaultConfig()\n    assert.Equal(t, \"8080\", cfg.Port)\n    assert.Equal(t, false, cfg.Debug)\n    // ...\n}\n```\n\n**Python testing** (planned, not implemented):\n- Framework: `pytest>=7.4.0`, `pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0`, `pytest-cov>=4.1.0`, `pytest-mock>=3.11.0`\n- File naming: `test_*.py` in `tests/` directory\n- Fixtures: `tmp_path` for isolated workspace testing\n- Coverage gate: >= 80% via `pytest --cov=agentcube`\n- Linting: `ruff check agentcube/`, `mypy agentcube/`\n- T/C ratio requirement: > 0.4 (40 lines of test per 100 lines of code)\n\n**TDD Manifest** (`testing/agentcube_tdd_manifest.md`):\nDefines required test cases per component (Workload Manager, Router, Session Store, PicoD, SDK/CLI).\n\n---\n\n### 7. Package Configuration Details\n\n**Go module** (`go.mod`):\n```\nmodule github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube\ngo 1.25.0\n```\n\nKey dependencies: Gin, controller-runtime, k8s.io/client-go v0.34.1, go-redis/v9, golang-jwt/jwt/v5, prometheus, testify.\n\n**Planned Python CLI** (`cmd/cli/pyproject.toml` -- not yet created):\n```toml\n[project]\nname = \"agentcube\"\nrequires-python = \">=3.10\"\ndependencies = [\n    \"typer[all]>=0.9.0\",\n    \"pydantic>=2.0.0\",\n    \"pyyaml>=6.0\",\n    \"httpx>=0.24.0\",\n    \"docker>=6.0.0\",\n    \"rich>=13.0.0\",\n    \"packaging>=23.0\",\n    \"importlib-resources>=6.0.0\",\n    \"semver>=3.0.0\",\n]\n\n[project.optional-dependencies]\nk8s = [\"kubernetes>=28.0.0\"]\ndev = [\"pytest>=7.4.0\", \"pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0\", \"pytest-cov>=4.1.0\", \"ruff>=0.1.0\", \"mypy>=1.5.0\", \"pre-commit>=3.3.0\", \"kubernetes>=28.0.0\"]\ntest = [\"pytest>=7.4.0\", \"pytest-asyncio>=0.21.0\", \"pytest-cov>=4.1.0\", \"pytest-mock>=3.11.0\", \"httpx-mock>=0.10.0\"]\n\n[project.scripts]\nkubectl-agentcube = \"agentcube.cli.main:app\"\n\n[tool.setuptools]\npackages = [\"agentcube\", \"agentcube.cli\", \"agentcube.runtime\", \"agentcube.operations\", \"agentcube.services\"]\n```\n\n**No Makefile exists** in the project currently.\n\n---\n\n### 8. Key Design/Spec Documents for ST-3 and Pack Command\n\n| File | Path | Description |\n|------|------|-------------|\n| Full Design | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/design.md` | AR-020 pack command -- complete design with code samples (798 lines) |\n| Base CLI Design | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cli-toolkit/design.md` | All 5 CLI commands, all runtime classes, all services (400 lines) |\n| Base CLI Spec | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cli-toolkit/spec.md` | Gherkin-style requirements for all CLI commands (197 lines) |\n| Delta Spec | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-020/delta-spec.md` | Additional pack-specific scenarios (313 lines) |\n| Proposal | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-020/proposal.md` | Scope, impact, alternatives, acceptance criteria (272 lines) |\n| Tasks | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-020/tasks.md` | Task template (TODO placeholders only, 32 lines) |\n| SDD Prompt | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/.sdd_prompt.md` | The prompt used to generate design.md |\n\n---\n\n### 9. Summary of Key Findings\n\n1. **The project is primarily a Go codebase** with 4 server-side binaries (agentd, picod, router, workloadmanager) and extensive Go test coverage.\n\n2. **The Python CLI (`cmd/cli/`) does NOT exist yet** -- zero `.py` files in the entire repository. However, it has been exhaustively designed across multiple documents.\n\n3. **AR-020 (CLI pack command)** is the most mature design document, with complete implementation code samples, but the `tasks.md` file is still a skeleton with TODO placeholders.\n\n4. **No `pyproject.toml`, `setup.py`, or any Python packaging files exist** -- these are only described in the design documents.\n\n5. **The change request system** uses a 4-file pattern (proposal.md, design.md, delta-spec.md, tasks.md) with ST-3 as the design completion gate.\n\n6. **Go testing** uses `testify/assert` with table-driven tests. **Python testing** (planned) uses pytest with tmp_path fixtures and 80% coverage gate.\n\n7. **The pack command pipeline** is: `pack -> build -> publish -> invoke`, with `PackRuntime` being the first runtime class to implement.\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_2871404faffeY7CDAMEBOr2j0m","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775850224385,"end":1775850424192}}}}
