{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775850430123,"sessionID":"ses_287142419ffeQOq2kV3FLICynY","part":{"id":"prt_d78ef19d5001VBpk8Uu2oiLcnV","messageID":"msg_d78ef07cf001IAn79aoue50Xfc","sessionID":"ses_287142419ffeQOq2kV3FLICynY","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_04c9fc08459845b8afabc466","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-020/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-020/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-020: CLI pack 命令 — Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Context\n4: \n5: - **Module:** cmd/cli\n6: - **Language:** Python\n7: - **Size:** M\n8: - **Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/design.md`, `cli-toolkit/spec.md`\n9: \n10: ## Delta Requirements\n11: \n12: ### Requirement: Workspace validation — not a directory\n13: \n14: #### Scenario: Workspace path exists but is a file\n15: - **GIVEN** the user provides `--workspace` pointing to a regular file (not a directory)\n16: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_workspace_structure` runs\n17: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with a message indicating the path is not a directory\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ### Requirement: Workspace validation — Java-specific\n22: \n23: #### Scenario: Java workspace without pom.xml\n24: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"java\"`\n25: - **WHEN** no `pom.xml` exists in the workspace root directory\n26: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating `pom.xml` is required for Java projects\n27: \n28: ---\n29: \n30: ### Requirement: Metadata loading with fallback chain\n31: \n32: #### Scenario: Primary metadata file exists\n33: - **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` exists in the workspace root\n34: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata` runs\n35: - **THEN** the system SHALL load and parse `agent_metadata.yaml` as `AgentMetadata`\n36: \n37: #### Scenario: Primary missing, first fallback exists\n38: - **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` does not exist but `agent.yaml` exists in the workspace root\n39: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata` runs\n40: - **THEN** the system SHALL load and parse `agent.yaml` as `AgentMetadata`\n41: \n42: #### Scenario: Primary and first fallback missing, second fallback exists\n43: - **GIVEN** neither `agent_metadata.yaml` nor `agent.yaml` exists, but `metadata.yaml` exists in the workspace root\n44: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata` runs\n45: - **THEN** the system SHALL load and parse `metadata.yaml` as `AgentMetadata`\n46: \n47: #### Scenario: No metadata file exists — create from CLI options\n48: - **GIVEN** none of `agent_metadata.yaml`, `agent.yaml`, or `metadata.yaml` exist in the workspace root\n49: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._load_or_create_metadata` runs\n50: - **THEN** the system SHALL create a new `AgentMetadata` instance using CLI-provided options and inferred defaults\n51: \n52: ---\n53: \n54: ### Requirement: Metadata merge — CLI overrides\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: CLI `--agent-name` overrides existing metadata\n57: - **GIVEN** existing metadata has `agent_name: \"old-agent\"`\n58: - **WHEN** the user passes `--agent-name \"new-agent\"`\n59: - **THEN** `PackRuntime._apply_option_overrides` SHALL set `metadata.agent_name` to `\"new-agent\"`\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: CLI `--language` overrides existing metadata\n62: - **GIVEN** existing metadata has `language: \"python\"`\n63: - **WHEN** the user passes `--language \"java\"`\n64: - **THEN** the system SHALL update `metadata.language` to `\"java\"` and re-validate via Pydantic validators\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: CLI `--entrypoint` overrides existing metadata\n67: - **GIVEN** existing metadata has `entrypoint: \"python main.py\"`\n68: - **WHEN** the user passes `--entrypoint \"python app.py\"`\n69: - **THEN** the system SHALL update `metadata.entrypoint` to `\"python app.py\"`\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: CLI `--port` overrides existing metadata\n72: - **GIVEN** existing metadata has `port: 8080`\n73: - **WHEN** the user passes `--port 9090`\n74: - **THEN** the system SHALL update `metadata.port` to `9090`\n75: \n76: #### Scenario: CLI `--build-mode` overrides existing metadata\n77: - **GIVEN** existing metadata has `build_mode: \"local\"`\n78: - **WHEN** the user passes `--build-mode \"cloud\"`\n79: - **THEN** the system SHALL update `metadata.build_mode` to `\"cloud\"`\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: CLI `--description` overrides existing metadata\n82: - **GIVEN** existing metadata has `description: \"old description\"`\n83: - **WHEN** the user passes `--description \"new description\"`\n84: - **THEN** the system SHALL update `metadata.description` to `\"new description\"`\n85: \n86: #### Scenario: CLI option is None, metadata value preserved\n87: - **GIVEN** existing metadata has `agent_name: \"my-agent\"`\n88: - **WHEN** the user does NOT pass `--agent-name` (value is `None`)\n89: - **THEN** the system SHALL preserve `metadata.agent_name` as `\"my-agent\"`\n90: \n91: ---\n92: \n93: ### Requirement: Entrypoint inference — Python\n94: \n95: #### Scenario: Python entrypoint inferred from first .py file\n96: - **GIVEN** `metadata.entrypoint` is `None` and `language` is `\"python\"`\n97: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._infer_entrypoint` runs and the workspace contains `main.py`\n98: - **THEN** the system SHALL return `\"python main.py\"` as the inferred entrypoint\n99: \n100: #### Scenario: Python entrypoint inferred from alternative .py file\n101: - **GIVEN** `metadata.entrypoint` is `None` and `language` is `\"python\"`\n102: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._infer_entrypoint` runs and the workspace contains `app.py` but no `main.py`\n103: - **THEN** the system SHALL return `\"python app.py\"` as the inferred entrypoint\n104: \n105: ---\n106: \n107: ### Requirement: Entrypoint inference — Java\n108: \n109: #### Scenario: Java entrypoint inferred as jar execution\n110: - **GIVEN** `metadata.entrypoint` is `None` and `language` is `\"java\"`\n111: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._infer_entrypoint` runs\n112: - **THEN** the system SHALL return `\"java -jar target/*.jar\"` or equivalent based on `pom.xml` analysis\n113: \n114: ---\n115: \n116: ### Requirement: Entrypoint inference — failure\n117: \n118: #### Scenario: No entrypoint inferable\n119: - **GIVEN** `metadata.entrypoint` is `None` and no inferable entrypoint exists for the language\n120: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._infer_entrypoint` runs\n121: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating entrypoint could not be inferred and must be provided via `--entrypoint`\n122: \n123: ---\n124: \n125: ### Requirement: Python compatibility validation\n126: \n127: #### Scenario: Python workspace has requirements.txt\n128: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"python\"` and `requirements.txt` exists in the workspace root\n129: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_python_compatibility` runs\n130: - **THEN** the system SHALL pass without error\n131: \n132: #### Scenario: Python workspace missing requirements.txt\n133: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"python\"` and `metadata.requirements_file` is `\"requirements.txt\"`\n134: - **WHEN** `requirements.txt` does not exist in the workspace root\n135: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_python_compatibility` runs\n136: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating the dependency file is missing\n137: \n138: #### Scenario: Python custom requirements file exists\n139: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"python\"` and `metadata.requirements_file` is `\"deps.txt\"`\n140: - **WHEN** `deps.txt` exists in the workspace root\n141: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_python_compatibility` runs\n142: - **THEN** the system SHALL pass without error\n143: \n144: ---\n145: \n146: ### Requirement: Java compatibility validation\n147: \n148: #### Scenario: Java workspace has valid pom.xml\n149: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"java\"` and `pom.xml` exists with valid XML\n150: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_java_compatibility` runs\n151: - **THEN** the system SHALL pass without error\n152: \n153: #### Scenario: Java workspace has invalid pom.xml\n154: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"java\"` and `pom.xml` exists but is not valid XML\n155: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_java_compatibility` runs\n156: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating invalid `pom.xml`\n157: \n158: ---\n159: \n160: ### Requirement: Dependency processing — Python\n161: \n162: #### Scenario: Python dependencies processed from requirements.txt\n163: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"python\"` and `requirements.txt` exists\n164: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._process_python_dependencies` runs\n165: - **THEN** the system SHALL read and validate the contents of `requirements.txt`\n166: \n167: #### Scenario: Python custom requirements file processed\n168: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"python\"` and `metadata.requirements_file` is `\"deps.txt\"`\n169: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._process_python_dependencies` runs\n170: - **THEN** the system SHALL read and validate `deps.txt` instead of `requirements.txt`\n171: \n172: ---\n173: \n174: ### Requirement: Dependency processing — Java\n175: \n176: #### Scenario: Java dependencies processed from pom.xml\n177: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"java\"` and `pom.xml` exists\n178: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._process_java_dependencies` runs\n179: - **THEN** the system SHALL parse `pom.xml` to extract dependency information\n180: \n181: ---\n182: \n183: ### Requirement: Dockerfile generation — Python\n184: \n185: #### Scenario: Generate Python Dockerfile when none exists\n186: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"python\"` and no `Dockerfile` exists in the workspace\n187: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._generate_dockerfile` runs\n188: - **THEN** the system SHALL call `_generate_python_dockerfile` and write the result to `{workspace}/Dockerfile`\n189: \n190: #### Scenario: Python Dockerfile includes required directives\n191: - **GIVEN** `PackRuntime._generate_python_dockerfile` is called with `metadata.port=8080` and `metadata.entrypoint=\"python main.py\"`\n192: - **WHEN** generating the Dockerfile content\n193: - **THEN** the output SHALL include: a base Python image, `WORKDIR`, copy of workspace files, `pip install -r requirements.txt`, `EXPOSE 8080`, and `CMD [\"python\", \"main.py\"]`\n194: \n195: #### Scenario: Existing Dockerfile is preserved\n196: - **GIVEN** a `Dockerfile` already exists in the workspace root\n197: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._generate_dockerfile` runs\n198: - **THEN** the system SHALL NOT overwrite the existing `Dockerfile` and SHALL return the existing path\n199: \n200: ---\n201: \n202: ### Requirement: Dockerfile generation — Java\n203: \n204: #### Scenario: Generate Java Dockerfile when none exists\n205: - **GIVEN** `metadata.language` is `\"java\"` and no `Dockerfile` exists in the workspace\n206: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._generate_dockerfile` runs\n207: - **THEN** the system SHALL call `_generate_java_dockerfile` and write the result to `{workspace}/Dockerfile`\n208: \n209: #### Scenario: Java Dockerfile includes multi-stage build\n210: - **GIVEN** `PackRuntime._generate_java_dockerfile` is called with `metadata.port=8080`\n211: - **WHEN** generating the Dockerfile content\n212: - **THEN** the output SHALL include: a Maven build stage (copy `pom.xml`, run `mvn package`), a runtime stage with JAR execution, `EXPOSE 8080`, and `CMD` using `metadata.entrypoint`\n213: \n214: ---\n215: \n216: ### Requirement: Pack metadata update\n217: \n218: #### Scenario: Metadata updated after successful pack\n219: - **GIVEN** pack has completed successfully with resolved metadata and optional generated `Dockerfile`\n220: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._update_pack_metadata` runs\n221: - **THEN** the system SHALL save `agent_metadata.yaml` with the final `entrypoint`, `language`, `port`, `build_mode`, `description`, and `dockerfile_path` (if generated)\n222: \n223: ---\n224: \n225: ### Requirement: Output path preparation\n226: \n227: #### Scenario: Default output path is workspace root\n228: - **GIVEN** the user does NOT pass `--output`\n229: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._prepare_output_path` runs\n230: - **THEN** the system SHALL return the resolved workspace root as the output path\n231: \n232: #### Scenario: Custom output path is used\n233: - **GIVEN** the user passes `--output \"/tmp/packed-agent\"`\n234: - **WHEN** `PackRuntime._prepare_output_path` runs\n235: - **THEN** the system SHALL return `/tmp/packed-agent` as the output path, creating intermediate directories if needed\n236: \n237: ---\n238: \n239: ### Requirement: Pack error handling — verbose vs non-verbose\n240: \n241: #### Scenario: Pack failure without verbose\n242: - **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises an exception\n243: - **WHEN** the user did NOT pass `--verbose` on the `pack` subcommand\n244: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print `Error packaging agent: {e}` in red (no traceback) and exit with code `1`\n245: \n246: #### Scenario: Global verbose vs subcommand verbose\n247: - **GIVEN** the user passed `-v` on the root callback but NOT `--verbose` on `pack`\n248: - **WHEN** an error occurs during pack\n249: - **THEN** the traceback SHALL NOT be printed because `_handle_error` receives the subcommand's `verbose` flag which is `False`\n250: \n251: ---\n252: \n253: ### Requirement: Port validation via Pydantic\n254: \n255: #### Scenario: Port within valid range accepted\n256: - **GIVEN** the user passes `--port 8080`\n257: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` validators run (via `validate_port`)\n258: - **THEN** the port SHALL be accepted (range 1–65535)\n259: \n260: #### Scenario: Port below valid range rejected\n261: - **GIVEN** the user passes `--port 0`\n262: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` validators run (via `validate_port`)\n263: - **THEN** Pydantic SHALL raise `ValidationError` rejecting the invalid port\n264: \n265: #### Scenario: Port above valid range rejected\n266: - **GIVEN** the user passes `--port 70000`\n267: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` validators run (via `validate_port`)\n268: - **THEN** Pydantic SHALL raise `ValidationError` rejecting the invalid port\n269: \n270: ---\n271: \n272: ### Requirement: Build mode validation via Pydantic\n273: \n274: #### Scenario: Valid build mode \"local\" accepted\n275: - **GIVEN** the user passes `--build-mode \"local\"`\n276: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` validators run (via `validate_build_mode`)\n277: - **THEN** the build mode SHALL be accepted and normalized to lowercase\n278: \n279: #### Scenario: Valid build mode \"cloud\" accepted\n280: - **GIVEN** the user passes `--build-mode \"cloud\"`\n281: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` validators run (via `validate_build_mode`)\n282: - **THEN** the build mode SHALL be accepted and normalized to lowercase\n283: \n284: #### Scenario: Invalid build mode rejected\n285: - **GIVEN** the user passes `--build-mode \"hybrid\"`\n286: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` validators run (via `validate_build_mode`)\n287: - **THEN** Pydantic SHALL raise `ValidationError` rejecting the unsupported build mode\n288: \n289: ---\n290: \n291: ### Requirement: Language validation via Pydantic\n292: \n293: #### Scenario: Unsupported language rejected\n294: - **GIVEN** the user passes `--language \"nodejs\"`\n295: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` validators run (via `validate_language`)\n296: - **THEN** Pydantic SHALL raise `ValidationError` rejecting the unsupported language (only `python` and `java` allowed)\n297: \n298: #### Scenario: Language case normalization\n299: - **GIVEN** the user passes `--language \"Python\"`\n300: - **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` validators run (via `validate_language`)\n301: - **THEN** the language SHALL be accepted and normalized to `\"python\"`\n302: \n303: ---\n304: \n305: ## File changes\n306: \n307: | File | Action | Description |\n308: |------|--------|-------------|\n309: | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Modify | `pack` command implementation with Typer options and error handling |\n310: | `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | Modify | `PackRuntime` class with all pack lifecycle methods |\n311: | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Modify | `MetadataService.load_metadata` with fallback chain |\n312: | `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | Modify | `MetadataOptions` dataclass for CLI option merging |\n313: | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Modify | Dockerfile generation helpers if not already present |\n\n(End of file - total 313 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-020: CLI pack 命令 — Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** cmd/cli\n- **Language:** Python\n- **Size:** M\n- **Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/design.md`, `cli-toolkit/spec.md`\n\n## Delta Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Workspace validation — not a directory\n\n#### Scenario: Workspace path exists but is a file\n- **GIVEN** the user provides `--workspace` pointing to a regular file (not a directory)\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_workspace_structure` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with a message indicating the path is not a directory\n\n---\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-020/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775850430111,"end":1775850430119}}}}
